White Lion, born Chibuike Steven Igbokwe, is regarded by many as an upcoming talent with the potential to go a long way in the African music industry. This observation is backed by his consistency and work ethics so far. His desire to make his mark and create a niche for himself has been his propellant since he decided to go professional with his musical career in 2012/2013. Born to Nigerian parents in Lagos, but based in South Africa, it was only until 2018 that he began recording professionally. This led to the release of several singles CHAMPAGNE, OBI and ‘FINE GIRL’. later in the year. He continued with a string of singles in 2019, the first, ‘Hustle’ a single produced by RealOnTheBeat, followed by “DRIP UP and OPEN & CLOSE”. 2020 has so far proven itself as an unprecedented year. Seen by many music pundits as the break out year for a lot of upcoming acts, White Lion wasn’t left out. His single “Pray For Me” a motivational mid-tempo track released in July got him the attention he has been craving. He is currently signed to White Lion Empire an Independent label he founded to help distribute and market his music. His musical favorites include Jay Z, Duncan Mighty, Drake, Burna boy, Wizkid & 2face Idibia aka 2Baba to list a few. He is currently working on his debut album which he hopes will be released later in the year or early 2021.